# macOS launchd setup for <service>-mcp

Run the MCP server as a persistent user-level daemon. Auto-starts on login, auto-restarts on crash, survives reboots.

## The plist

Save at `~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.<service>-mcp.plist`. Replace placeholders before installing.

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.<service>-mcp</string>

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
        <string>BINARY_ABSOLUTE_PATH</string>
        <!-- Add flags as needed -->
    </array>

    <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
    <dict>
        <key>CONFIG_PATH</key>
        <string>/Users/YOUR_USER/.<service>.yaml</string>

        <key>PATH</key>
        <string>/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/opt/homebrew/bin</string>
    </dict>

    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>

    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <true/>

    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>/Users/YOUR_USER/Library/Logs/<service>-mcp.log</string>

    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>/Users/YOUR_USER/Library/Logs/<service>-mcp.log</string>
</dict>
</plist>
```

### Required substitutions

| Placeholder | What to put |
|---|---|
| `BINARY_ABSOLUTE_PATH` | Output of `which <binary-name>` — must be absolute, no `$HOME` or `~` |
| `YOUR_USER` | Your macOS username (or replace with `/Users/$(whoami)` when running configure.sh) |
| `<service>` | Your service name (e.g., `pinecone`, `notion`, `linear`) |

## Install commands

```bash
# Load the plist (since macOS 11+)
launchctl bootstrap gui/$UID ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.<service>-mcp.plist

# Check it's running
launchctl list | grep <service>-mcp

# Watch the logs
tail -f ~/Library/Logs/<service>-mcp.log
```

## Reload after editing the plist

launchd doesn't pick up plist changes automatically. After any edit:

```bash
launchctl bootout gui/$UID ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.<service>-mcp.plist
launchctl bootstrap gui/$UID ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.<service>-mcp.plist
```

## Stop / uninstall

```bash
# Stop
launchctl bootout gui/$UID ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.<service>-mcp.plist

# Remove the plist
rm ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.<service>-mcp.plist

# Remove the credential file (only if you're done with this MCP entirely)
rm ~/.<service>.yaml
```

## Common gotchas

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Daemon shows `exit code 78` | Path in `ProgramArguments` has `$HOME` or `~` | Use absolute path; plist doesn't expand env-style paths |
| Daemon starts, then exits immediately | Binary on `PATH` for your shell but not for launchd | Add `PATH` explicitly in `EnvironmentVariables` |
| Logs are empty | `StandardOutPath` directory doesn't exist | `mkdir -p ~/Library/Logs/` |
| Daemon won't reload after edit | Need to `bootout` before `bootstrap` | Run both commands; launchd doesn't auto-reload |
| `Bootstrap failed: 5: Input/output error` | Plist already loaded | Run `bootout` first |
| Daemon starts but Claude can't see it | Wrong URL/port in Claude settings.json | Verify port matches what the binary listens on |

## Logs

The log file at `~/Library/Logs/<service>-mcp.log` is your debugging best friend. When something's wrong:

```bash
tail -50 ~/Library/Logs/<service>-mcp.log
```

Common log signals:

- `Listening on http://0.0.0.0:PORT` — server is up
- `OAuth error` — credential issue, check the config file
- `ImportError` — package install incomplete; re-run `pipx install`
- `Address already in use` — port conflict; change the port or kill the conflicting process
